article.headline: Austin Peay 73, SE Missouri State 62
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Maurice Hampton scored 20 points, including six free throws in the last nine seconds, as Austin Peay held off Southeast Missouri 73-62 Monday night. Zac Schlader added 19 points for the Governors (12-10, 7-6 Ohio Valley Conference), including 9-of-13 from the field. Southeast Missouri (6-14, 3-11) trailed the entire second half but got as close as 5, 65-60, with 25 seconds left. Austin Peay's final eight points were all free throws, six by Hampton and two by Fernandez Lockett. The Governors were 17-of-21, or 81 percent, from the line for the game, all in the second half. The Redhawks were led by Roy Booker with 22 points and Paul Paradoski and Terrick Willoughby with 11 each. Southeast Missouri shot just 33.9 percent for the game, with the Governors hitting 44.1 percent. Austin Peay led 35-19 at halftime. The Redhawks controlled the boards, with 42 to Austin Peay's 35, led by Waylon Francis with 9.
